      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>April 20 analysis about testimony of Atty Gen Alberto R Gonzales before Senate Judiciary Committee referred incorrectly to power of Congress to remove attorney general from office</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A news analysis article yesterday about the testimony of Attorney General Alberto R. Gonzales before the Senate Judiciary Committee referred incorrectly to the power of Congress to remove an attorney general from office. Under the Constitution, civil officers of the United States government may be removed upon impeachment by the House of Representatives and trial in the Senate. Congress is not powerless to remove the attorney general.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
